{"serial": "16002", "department_serial": 16, "code": "AR0031", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Festival And Curating Practice", "ch": "節慶活動與策展實作"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Huang, Lan-Yan"], "ch": ["黃蘭燕"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "C2", "room": "204"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "藝術學研究所碩士班", "en": "MA in Art Studies"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 18, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "英雄之旅，16周的啟程。\n\n節慶活動充斥我們的生活，無論是傳統或創新的活動。這些活動亦是活絡地方經濟、復振文化、凝聚認同的方式；在節慶活動中，展示設計則為溝通文化內容的型式。而策展是說故事的方式，這個人人都需要故事的時代，用故事作文化溝通，是文化工作者的能力，本課程將培育學生策展基礎概念與入門方法。\n本課程目標在培養學生具規畫及執行文化活動的能力，包括以下目標：\n1、引導學生思考文化節慶活動的本質與內涵，包括重大節慶介紹、台灣經典節慶。\n2、帶領學生認識節慶與展覽的籌備、設計、財務、行銷、執行等各階段作業。", "en": "Hero‘s Journey, A 16-Week Expedition\n\nThis is a heroic journey co-created with classmates and launched with goals, methods, and actions.\n\n1. Guide students to think about the nature and connotation of cultural festivals, including introduction to major festivals and classic festivals in Taiwan.\n\n2. Lead students to understand the preparation, design, finance, marketing, and execution of festivals and exhibitions."}, "outline": {"ch": "•W1—課程介紹、作業說明\n•W2—物件的力量—成為說故事的人\n•W3— 策展作為社會溝通的工具\n•W4—策展流程I觀眾研究\n•W5—策展流程II敘事手法\n•W6—展覽素材、互動與行銷 (移地教學暫定寶藏巖)\n•W7—連假．停課\n•W8—期中分享會：個人故事箱\n•W9—節慶活動的本質與文化意義\n•W10—節慶活動改變社會的可能：日本瀨戶內海藝術祭\n•W11—節慶活動的反思\n•W12—跨域資源協作\n•W13—節慶活動與地方創生（桃園案例）\n•W14—節慶活動的財務規畫、進度管理\n•W15—節慶活動的人力、服務、設備、效益評估\n•W16—期末分享會—團隊藝術行動實作", "en": "• W1—Course introduction, assignment instructions\n• W2—The Power of Objects—Become a Storyteller\n• W3—Curation as a social communication tool\n• W4—Curatorial Process I Audience Research\n• W5—Curatorial Process II Narrative Techniques\n• W6—Exhibition materials, interaction and marketing (relocation teaching tentatively decided at Treasure Rock)\n• W7—continuous holidays. Suspension of classes\n• W8—Midterm Sharing Session: Personal Story Box\n• W9—The essence and cultural significance of festivals\n• W10—The possibility of festivals to change society: Japan’s Seto Inland Sea Art Festival\n• W11 – Reflections on festive events\n• W12—Cross-domain resource collaboration\n• W13—Festival activities and place creation (Taoyuan case)\n• W14—Financial planning and progress management of festival activities\n• W15—Evaluation of manpower, services, equipment, and benefits of festival activities\n• W16—Final Sharing Session—Team Art Action Implementation"}, "textbook": {"ch": "<從直島啟航的瀨戶內海國際藝術祭>福武總一郎、北川富朗，遠流出版。2017\n<節慶與活動管理>， Johnny Allen, William O’Toole, Ian McDonnell著，五觀出版。2004", "en": "Festival and Special Event Management，Johnny Allen, William O’Toole, Robert Harris, Ian McDonnell"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "80", "en": "80"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "課堂討論20％\n個人作業30％\n藝術行動40％\n出席率10％", "en": "discussion 20％\nhomework 30％\nart project 40％\nAttendance rate10％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "周四，早上8-9點", "en": "thu.8-9AM"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "校外教學4小時以上、分組報告指導每組至少一小時以上。", "en": "More than 4 hours of off-campus teaching, and at least one hour of group reporting and guidance for each group."}, "domain": {"ch": "文化行政", "en": "文化行政"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知能", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "邏輯與批判能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "語文表達與溝通", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "多元與國際視野", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "自主學習", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "統合與創新能力", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭